wpkg (0.9.7) trusty; urgency=high

  * Now no longer You no longer have to supply the "--repository" argument
    when installing from internal repositories (contents of core/sources.list).
    Once you've added a repository to your sources list, --install will
    automatically look for the package plus any dependencies and install them.

