wpkg (0.9.5) stable unstable; urgency=medium

  * Applied a couple of patches by Mathieu SCHROETER to fix the compilation
    under MinGW.
  * Mathieu also found a fix to main() so Unicode if fully supported.
  * Applied a patch by Trent Clarke to fix the basic authentication when
    using HTTP to retrieve packages. A \r\n was missing.
  * Fixed a problem with os_stat() that would throw when checking paths
    representing a URI.
  * Fixed 3 errors that would say "validate removal" instead of "repository".
  * Fixed the -V so it works with control.info files.
  * Fixed the propagation of the --debug flag when building sources or
    compiling binary packages.
  * Fixed the --list-index-packages so it supports paths.
  * Moved the ChangeLog to the debian/changelog file instead.

