wpkg (0.9.4) stable unstable; urgency=medium

  * Applied a patch by Trent Clarke to fix big problems with large trees
    of dependencies so all possibilities do get tested as expected.
  * Fixed the problems with architectures not being canonicalized when
    determining whether a script should be added or not.
  * Fixed architecture <= and >= operators.
  * Fixed the output when vendor is defined, but all three parameters are
    "any" (we expect "any" as a return value of to_string()).
  * Properly detect "validate" scripts.
  * Detect additional shell scripts to determine that a script is for Unix.
  * Do not add any scripts to source packages (mistake?)
  * Check whether a processor name include invalid characters in case a
    pattern is used to match the name.
  * Updated the copyright date of all files to 2014.

