wpkg (0.9.0) stable unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added support for an area in the Section field.
  * Added advanced --help functions, try: wpkg --help help
  * Added support for reading changelog & copyright files.
  * Added support to create source packages.
  * Added support to create binary packages from source packages.
  * Added support for long filenames in tarballs (GNU extension/PaxHeader.)
  * Added support for user defined validation scripts.
  * Added support for global validation scripts.
  * Added --autoremove to remove now unused implicitly installed packages.
  * Added alias support for command line arguments.
  * Added --[enforce-]path-length-limit to build sensible packages.
  * Added support to manage build numbers.
  * Added support for a Minimum-Upgradable-Version field.
  * Added support for the --reconfigure command.
  * Added support for full rollback of installation or removal.
  * Added more ways to access variables in field (control) files.
  * Added support for a vendor in architectures.
  * Added pkgconfig like support (i.e. reading of .pc files.)
  * Added a Component field to use along the Distribution field.
  * Added many new unit tests and upgraded many existing tests.
  * Added the --reconfigure command to re-run the configuration scripts.
  * Added doxygen documentation

  * Redesign the loading of control files with the field_file.
  * Redesign the log feature with C++ capabilities.
  * Redesign the temporary directory and always use /tmp/wpkg-<pid> under
    Unix and $TEMP/wpkg-<pid> under MS-Windows plus auto-delete it on exit,
    so content based functions (--contents) do not require a --root anymore.
  * Implemented a class to handle all Debian architectures seemlessly.
  * Changed win32/win64 to mswindows as the operating system name.
  * Added alias --verify-fields for --validate-fields.
  * Made --status an alias of --field.
  * Changed the old --status code to print as --status-fd, but using the
    --package-status command because we do not support an 'fd'.
  * Put support for the Distribution field back, checked at install time.
  * Put support for --force-distribution back to allow any Distribution.
  * Change the handling of the Distribution field.
  * Updated different scripts to get better packages, coverage info, etc.
  * Changed support for long filenames so UNC is used in many more cases even
    when path is not absolute or too many things fail.
 
  * Fixed several improper references in log messages.
  * Fixed the --force-architecture, actually test the flag!
  * Fixed the --fsys-tarfile which would crash with files over 64Kb
  * Fixed a missing version test of an unpacked package that needs
    configuration (we would accept any version)
  * Fixed test of unpacked packages to auto-configure to properly use the
    --force-configure-any instead of --force-depends-version
  * Fixed dependency search to test installed packages after we checked
    for explicit packages; this will allows us to avoid longer searches
  * Fixed the Hold status check when --configure is used.
  * Fixed the time zone in the Date field under MS-Windows
  * Fixed time value so we keep them as 64 bit values.
  * Fixed some problems with reading files which names use Unicode.
  * Fixed the dynamic libraries and the static libraries are still working
    fine (requires a newer version of cmake to work right)

 -- Alexis Wilke <alexis@m2osw.com>  Tue, 11 Jun 2013 07:37:18 -0800

