wpkg (0.8.0) stable unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added support for MS-Windows network filenames (UNC)
  * Added support to recognize protocols (smb and http)
  * Added support for long filenames (over 260 characters)
  * Added support for HTTP protocol to read files from websites (for --install)
  * Added a TCP/IP client and server class
  * Added support for configuration files (system & user)
  * Added support for the environment variable WPKG_OPTIONS
  * Added support for wpkg to self-upgrade
  * Added and enhanced inline documentation and errors
  * Added support for directories and symbolic links in filesmetadata
  * Added a vendor string to the library
  * Added --architecture, --os, --processor, --triplet, and --vendor to wpkg
  * Added a shell() command to libexpr
  * Added a vendor() command to the library for control files
  * Added support for repository indexes and access
  * Added support for updates and upgrades from repositories
  * Added unit tests with Qt support and that can run under MS-Windows
  * Added a new error in the libexpr when a variable is expected and not found
  * Added support for wide strings in libexpr and other parts of the software
  * Added a --log-output to save logs in a local file
  * Added a selection state of "Hold" to prevent auto-upgrades if needed
  * Added a --dry-run to only run validations of install/remove commands
  * Added a callback for Ctrl-C to better control interruption
  * Added support for UTF-16 characters in filenames under MS-Windows
  * Added package support so we can create wpkg packages for distribution
  * Added simple manual pages for Unix distributions
  * Added the --compress and --decompress commands
  * Added an --md5sums to create an md5sums file from packages and other files
  * Added compressed ChangeLog to the package using wpkg
  * Made necessary changes to compile under darwin, mingw, and cygwin
  * Moved the architecture determination to libversion.c so it is public
  * Enhanced the operating system and processor detection in CMakeLists.txt
  * Enhanced the output and logging capabilities
  * Properly prevent files from being used from the WPKG directory
  * Make use of the --validate-fields when installing packages
  * Changed test on load package: use full path as an invalid duplicate test
  * Updated the dar tool to support HTTP
  * Skip "." and ".." from reading directories under MS-Windows
  * Prevent usage of special MS-Windows filenames such as COM1 and LPT3
  * Prevent usage of characters not supported in filenames under MS-Windows
  * In packages, prevent filenames that start/end with a space
  * In packages, prevent filenames that end with a period
  * Prevent using SUID/GUID in filesmetadata when creating a source package
  * Prevent the use of the "shlibs:" variable name
  * Changed the catch() in main() into an exit(1) instead of re-throw
  * Changed the Linux behavior to also use the exit(1) on error
  * Changed the catch() to log the exception message
  * Removed unused functions in the wpkgar_install class
  * Enhanced the output of control file errors with a filename and line number
  * Made the is_architecture_valid() a public function
  * Fixed the inter-drive installation capability under MS-Windows
  * Fixed the --install so it deletes the files that disappeared on upgrade
  * Fixed the installation order, if a depends on b, install b first
  * Fixed dependency version checks while installing
  * Fixed the fact that a failure of preinst was not generating an error
  * Fixed an installation bug where postinst would not get executed
  * Fixed the use of --instdir for installations and removals
  * Fixed overwrite tests so it works as expected in all cases
  * Fixed the backup so it can delete new files if no old files existed
  * Fixed the --remove/--purge against unpacked packages
  * Fixed the --configure and --deconfigure so they work as expected
  * Fixed the state on --unpack
  * Fixed the handling of the default operator in the output, it is '>='
  * Fixed the --unpack so it can be used to upgrade already unpacked packages
  * Fixed wpkg so it exits with 1 on errors
  * Fixed the DLL so it is possible to link against them properly
  * Fixed several operators in libexpr so they loop as expected
  * Fixed several floating point operations in variable.cpp
  * Fixed the --remove dependency check when multiple packages are specified
  * Fixed the CMakeLists.txt to properly install everything
  * Fixed the use of optional_multiple_argument in the advgetopt class
  * Fixed the printing of errors + usage, that made it hard to find the errors
  * Fixed the filesmetadata parsing as 'p' is for FIFO (not 'f')
  * Fixed filesmetadata support of FIFO filenames
  * Fixed some error messages (better, include some filename, etc.)
  * Fixed several problems in the memfile implementation
  * Fixed the --output-filename to prevent drive specifications
  * Fixed the --exception to prevent drive specifications
  * Fixed a bug with the unlock() which would fail in some cases
  * Fixed a bug with the copying of the database and the wpkg-status file
  * Fixed the dar tool so it catches exceptions
  * Fixed the pow() command and use the 2nd parameter as expected

