  * Added support to define meta data for files externally
  * Added support to add special files without having to do so in the install
  * Added support for symbolic links under Unix
  * Added support for the Distribution field, checked at install time
  * Added --build-and-install to immediately install after a build
  * Added --numbers to show user/group/mode as numbers in --contents
  * Added a shared version of all the libraries for 3rd party development
  * Added the libtld to support checking URI addresses in control files
  * Added a pack script to generate the Debian like wpkg packages
  * Added function distribution() which returns the wpkg distribution
  * Added function architecture() which returns the wpkg architecture
  * Added --force-any-distribution to allow installing any package
  * Added check of Standards-Version field, optional
  * Added checks on many more control file fields
  * Swapped display of long and short command line options
  * Remove the Build-Depends/Conflicts[-Indep] from non-source packages
  * Properly run prerm script when deconfiguring
  * Properly test that --output-filename and a .info are not used together
  * Forbidding lines that start with a period, a space, and something else
  * Fixed a bug with the bzip2 decompression that would fail in one case
  * Fixed the status after deconfiguring to "Unpacked"
  * Fixed the creation of directories, that is done although not yet backed up
  * Fixed order of command line options so it is alphabetical
  * Fixed a few tests that improperly checked paths as absolute
  * Fixed the time when variables/expressions get applied to control fields
  * Fixed the script calling convensions so paths/args can include spaces
  * Fixed documentation so as to avoid one directory level
  * Fixed unpacking over a read-only file
  * Fixed the C/C++ expression ?: operator right hand-side computation
  * Fixed the & expression, it was using ^ instead
  * Fixed the fmod() function, it needs 2 parameters
  * Fixed the TOK_INTEGER, in case of 0 it was missing an ungetc() call
  * Fixed the --help output so it is limited to 80 columns
  * Fixed several commands that tested for "_" only instead of "_/"
  * Fixed warnings in 32 & 64 bit Windows (size_t missused)
  * Fixed the naming for the z and bz2 libraries (wpkg_z, wpkg_bz2)
  * Fixed the library references of each library and tool
  * Fixed the dir_rewind() that would setup the position offset too soon
  * Fixed the mkdir_p() function to ignore C:/ at the start of paths
  * Fixed the size computation, f_block_size was unsigned
  * Fixed the ChangeLog format to match Debian
  * Fixed the installation of runtime versus development files
  * Fixed the Installed-Size and Extra-Size to be in Kb instead of bytes
  * Updated README to include information about DLL usage
  * Updated copyright notice to include 2013

